{"id":15098,"date":"2013-07-16T16:00:49","date_gmt":"2013-07-16T12:00:49","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=15098"},"modified":"2019-05-23T15:09:49","modified_gmt":"2019-05-23T11:09:49","slug":"niyyah-obligatory-sawm","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/16\/niyyah-obligatory-sawm\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Fasting: Making intention before days of obligatory fasting"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Hafsa reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<b>Whoever does not have the intention to fast before dawn, there is no fasting for him.<\/b>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Al-Tirmidhi said, &#8220;The meaning according to the people of knowledge is that the fast is invalid if intention is not made before sunrise in Ramadan, or for making up a Ramadan fast, or fasting for a vow. If one does not intend to do so in the night, it is not allowed. As for voluntary fasting, it is permissible to make an intention after morning; it is the opinion of Al-Shafi&#8217;i, Ahmad, and Ishaq.&#8221;<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 730<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/i>(authentic) according to Al-Suyuti<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062d\u064e\u0641\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e<b> \u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0644\u064e\u0645\u0652 \u064a\u064f\u062c\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0639\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0650\u0651\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0628\u0652\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0641\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0631\u0650 \u0641\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627 \u0635\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0647\u064f<\/b><\/p>\n<p align=\"