":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14904,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/10\/suhur-recite-fifty-ayat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15098,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Suhur: Prolonging pre-fasting meal before Fajr","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 10, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Zayd ibn Thabit reported: We ate the pre-fasting meal\u00a0with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and then we stood for prayer. It was asked, \u201cHow long was it between the two calls to prayer?\u201d Zayd said, \u201cIt was time enough to recite fifty verses from the Quran.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27566,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/15\/permission-not-fast-journey\/","url_meta":{"origin":15098,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Permission to fast or not on journey, whatever is easiest","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Hamzah ibn Amr asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, about fasting while traveling. The Prophet said, \u201cIf you wish, you may fast. And if you wish, you may break your fast.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1841, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1121 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28698,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/05\/children-fasting-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":15098,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Children fasting Ramadan if they are able","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Rabia\u2019 bint Mu\u2019awwidh reported: We would order our children to fast and we would make toys for them out of wool. If one of them cried for food, we would give them those toys until it was time to break fast. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1859, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1136 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33326,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/31\/fasting-ashura-9th-muharram\/","url_meta":{"origin":15098,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on &#8216;Ashura: Fasting day of &#8216;Ashura with 9th of Muharram","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 31, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Hakam ibn al-A\u2019raj reported: I went to Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, and I said, \u201cTell me about fasting the day of 'Ashura.\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cWhen you see the crescent of the month of al-Muharram, count the days and wake up to fast on the ninth\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{